.TH "lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_reset" 9 "lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_reset \- Prepare SLI4 device for pci slot reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_sli4_prep_dev_for_reset
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is called to prepare the SLI4 device for PCI slot reset. It
disables the device interrupt and pci device, and aborts the internal FCP
pending I/Os.
